args:
The egg hunt's only just begun, but things
are already heating up! Laranoa and Sylas
join the fray, and the prince's team struggles
to keep up. Eventually they come across a
girl named Fleur, who joins the team as
they redouble their efforts.

The prince and his friends are aiming
to win the egg hunt in hopes of seeing
their request granted. As they search
the forest for painted eggs...
Stop right there, fiend scum! Haaaaah!
What was that about? It seemed to be after\nthe painted eggs.
The heck would a fiend want with a\ntoy egg? You can't eat a toy egg, genius!
Maybe it just liked the pretty colors?
Whoa! That was close.\nHey—ack! My eggs!
You let it swipe 'em?!\nGet your head in the game, man!
...But alas, you're as careless as ever.\nYou may have grown, but you're still\nvery much a child.
Sylas... You're on the hunt too, then?
Hmph. Apparently it was only\na flesh wound.
That fiend's running off with your eggs!
And I'M running away with the win!\nLook out belooooow!
Remember how I said I'd stop trying to\nrecruit you and Sarisse as my lackeys?
I'm not TRYING anymore—I'm just gonna\ndo it! After I win the egg hunt, you won't\nhave a choice! Nya ha ha!
So you two better start thinking about\nwho's gonna kiss which boot!

Don't worry, it won't ALL be boot kissing.
Being village chief comes with some pretty
sweet perks, and I'll let you enjoy 'em too!
But first I gotta win this thing, so—toodles!
Crap! If she pulls out the win,\nwe're gonna have to leave the\nHalidom and live in her village!
Worry not. I would never allow anyone\nbut myself to defeat you.
What will you ask for if you win, Sylas?
I will ratify our tradition of solitude as law,\nand ensure that outsiders never be allowed\nto mingle with sylvans again.
What?! Come on, man, that's crazy.
Such measures are necessary when\nfaced with rabble-rousers like yourself.\nTo break tradition is to invite chaos.
You can't be serious. How's sylvan society\nsupposed to develop if we keep isolating\nourselves?

We've no need of outside influence. The
forests offer plentiful resources, and no
race better understands cultivation. Now,
if you'll excuse me; I have a win to secure.
Argh! Since when is he such a hardhead?!
He and Laranoa both seem pre-tty\nserious about winning...

And on top of that, we have fiends going
around stealing eggs. We'll need to keep
our wits about us if we hope to have a
chance at winning.
No freakin' way am I gonna lose to them!
Aah! What the—the ground's all muddy!\nI can't move!
This mud looks mega deep.\nI smell a pickle.
Just take one foot out before the\nother one sinks, ya ding-dongs!\nHere, watch me. Hup!
She makes it look like hopscotch!
Nya ha ha! Just one of my many\nspecial skills!
Psh, I can totally pull THAT off. Check it\nout, I—ACK! I'm sinking! HEEEEELP!
I found an egg! Buuut I think I also found\na beehive...
Is that all it takes to stay your hand?\nHmph. Watch closely.
Stay back, Sylas, you'll—\n...Wait, why the heck aren't\nthe bees attacking you?
I cloaked myself in an aromatic that, while\npleasant to most, is wholly unsavory to\ninsects. I call it ＂preparation.＂
There is little point in taking a leap if you\nhave no plan in place for the landing.
Psh, that's overkill. I'll just zip in and\nout before the bees even notice. Chaaarge!
Don't bring them over here, you idiot!\nEEEEEEK!
*pant* *pant* We're really not having\nmuch luck with these eggs.
Only because Luca keeps acting\nlike he's some invincible hero!
Sylas and Laranoa are the ones who\nwent and raised the stakes on us!
Should we revise our strategy?\nIt seems like all the eggs in this\narea have already been found.
Let's head deeper into the woods.\nThere should still be—
A b-bear! Should I...play dead?\nOkay Mr. Bear, I'm dead now—\ndon't mind me!
AAAH! Okay, nevermind, I'm outta here!
Stop! Don't turn your back to it!
Wh-who are you?! Wait, tell me \nlater—I gotta run!
Just stand still and LISTEN.\nDon't take your eyes off the bear.
When you're faced with a bear, ya gotta\nstay calm and wait for it to move on.\nIf you run, it's just gonna give chase.
So, are you lost? You get separated\nfrom your friends or something?
Excuse you, I'm not LOST!\nI'm an artist.

Art is a journey, you know? Sure, I might
be exploring new places I've never been,
and yeah, MAYBE I got a little turned
around—but I am NOT lost.
I AM, however, Fleur. An artist.\nWho does art.
Nice to meet you, Fleur.\nHow's your egg hunt going?
Wait, she's competition?! Maybe we\nshoulda left her to the bear...

Shut it, Luca. Still, what's up with you
freaking out back there? If you're gonna
walk in the woods, you really oughta
know how to handle bears.
Well...I guess that kinda stuff is just\noutside my expertise. I never really\ntook an interest.
Wh-what's wrong with that?! Art is GREAT.
Kinda hard to enjoy it if a bear eats\nyou for lunch, though. Maybe you\nshould head home.
No way! Nobody's gonna come between\nme and my dream—not you, not that bear,\nand DEFINITELY not me!
Yup! I'm going to revolutionize the\nart world, with a piece that fuses\nhuman and sylvan styles.
You know it! To make it happen, though,\nI need to study in a human town.
But the elders are so STUBBORN;\nthey won't let me leave the village.
So I'm gonna win the egg hunt, and then\nthey'll HAVE to let me go.
Heh, I love a girl who knows what\nshe wants!
You really think so?\nPeople usually laugh...

I'm always sayin' humans and sylvans
should spend more time together, but
makin' art to show people why? That's
somethin' I never woulda thought of!
Oh my gosh, YES—you get it!
They're like two paints on a palette.
Heh, yeah. Together they can make\nsomething great!
Hey, Fleur—you wanna team up with\nus on this egg hunt?
Y-you really wouldn't mind? It'd be nice to\nhave someone to talk to for a change...
He wanted to leave you to the bears a\nsecond ago! Ugh, this brother of mine.
Heh, same old Luca. Anyway, we can't\nreally leave her to roam the woods alone.
C'mon Fleur, let's go find a shortcut\nto get deeper into the forest!
Ooh, I think I know one actually!\nI grew up around here, see.
My mom used to tell me all about this\nforest when I was little, so I drew up a\nmap based on what she said.
Heh, shucks. Maps are just another\ntype of art, you know?
Anyway, everything we need to know about\nthe forest should be here, so all we gotta\ndo is follow it to victory!
Heh heh, all right—let's go, everyone!
